00:40:46.182 --> 00:40:50.981
Thank you. Yeah, that's a great question. So, to answer your first part, we have a sports scientist

00:40:50.981 --> 00:40:55.781
on staff who handles all of our sports performance data. We're slowly getting to the point where we

00:40:55.781 --> 00:41:02.742
can collaborate together more, but she handles most of that day-to-day. She's great. So,

00:41:03.541 --> 00:41:09.382
all of our players wear GPS units in-game and in training for us to track things around

00:41:10.182 --> 00:41:16.021
sprints, accelerations, decelerations, heart rate, all that kind of stuff. And in some leagues,

00:41:16.021 --> 00:41:21.062
that's required. In other leagues, it's voluntary. It's all up to the CBA. I think in our league,

00:41:21.062 --> 00:41:25.942
it's required. I've never seen any player not wear one. So, that's how they collect most of

00:41:25.942 --> 00:41:32.582
their data. The players also do fill out daily wellness surveys around sleep and whatnot.

00:41:32.582 --> 00:41:37.461
