a danger that they will start to optimize the way they play to improve their individual statistics

00:48:59.462 --> 00:49:03.621
rather than what is best for the team? This is a question that spans not just sports,

00:49:04.261 --> 00:49:07.862
but everything. If you've ever worked in a call center or managed a call center, you know that

00:49:07.862 --> 00:49:12.822
if you give people metrics that are time on call, they'll start to optimize for that at the

00:49:12.822 --> 00:49:18.021
detriment of their call quality. Does that happen in sports analytics too? Are the players

00:49:18.021 --> 00:49:23.781
self-aware of their stats? That is such a fun question. First of all, I do want to say we

00:49:23.781 --> 00:49:28.102
have some players that are super interested in data. One of the cool but also sad things

